The paper discusses a database management system (SciDB) that is designed for large-scale data storage and advanced analytics, making it relevant to the categories of database systems (cs.DB), distributed and parallel computing (cs.DC, cs.HPC), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of the D4M toolbox for implementing the benchmark, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
